-- Waiter: Severus Rabon
-- Occupation: waiter
-- Age: 31
-- Race: Human
-- Skin:  very dark
-- Hair: short black
-- Height: normal
-- Weight: petite
-- Clothes: Short sleeve black shirt. Brown Leather pants.
-- Personality: Severus used to be very laid back and lazy and even after he started his tavern. He stayed this way in all things that are not his daughter. When he had her he became a super worry wart, always wondering what would make her safe and happy.

-- Background: A poor man with a dream. He was born a single child. His parents loved and believed that he would be something, He lofted on this dream until hard reality smacked him in his face. When he finally was kicked out of his house he had no money and no skills. He tried random jobs around the city. He sucked at all of them and ended up homeless. For years he begged for money, until one day he had enough and found a way to make money for himself no matter how pathetic. He would go into the desert and gather sand rodents. He built a makeshift stand out of abandoned wood. This went over decent. He actually started to make quite a bit of money since he lived and worked out of a stand that cost him no money. He eventually used his money to pay dowry for a wife. He wanted a cute girl, any would have done. He chose the cheapest of the cute girls he could find, A women from a poor family that was elated to now have a business owner of a husband. He told her his lofty dreams and she worked hard to help him manage it. They eventually saved up enough to build an actual location to sell their sand rat, and that place grew into a general tavern. They have one daughter who cooks. His wife, Rose, passed away recently and so his daughter Linda is all that is left to him of her.

